list.name: Default Changelist
list.comment:
1) When you spin the coins (with the roll button), the table data shouldn't be *updated* until the roll animation is done so they're both in sync. Otherwise you can see if you won or lost just by looking at the table data, without waiting for the animation to finish. Just seems like better user experience.
2) Profit can be negative (if Amount Won is less than Amount Wagered), currently mine shows positive even though I know I am in negative cause I have more losses than wins.
3) Fix payout to show as "2.0x" (when you win) rather than "2.0 x". Also, when you lose, in the tables, payout should be 0x, not continuously show 2x, as the payout is 0x since they won nothing.
4) Show the last few rolled numbers above the roll button, example: https://gyazo.com/de53d18b21b4917dbb0bd64b19b24a54 -- they should be GREEN text when they win and GRAY text when they lose: #778192. Same thing should be done to: .dark span.loss CSS. Think this helps hide or blend in the losses a lot more. The red also looks a little bit weird on our site :).
